Supplementary Code: Transgenerational inheritance of impaired larval T cell development in zebrafish

Norimasa Iwanami, Divine-Fondzenyuy Lawir, Katarzyna Sikora, Connor Oâ€™Meara, Kohei Takeshita, Michael Schorpp, Thomas Boehm

Summary

This document provides the R code and accompanying explanations to reproduce Figures 1 e-f, 6 a-d, 7 b as well as Supplementary Figures 2 b-d and 5 a from the manuscript with working title â€œTransgenerational inheritance of impaired larval T cell development in zebrafishâ€ by Iwanami et al..
The analysis starts with SNP and coverage-filtered methylation ratios as well as tables with results of differential methylation analysis and walks the reader through the data processing underlying the manuscript figures. A copy of this document will be deposited on GitHub under https://github.com/katsikora/Iwanami2019_SupplementaryCodeAndData_A upon publication. The code is formatted in a way to facilitate understanding and interpretation by a lay R user. This code is authored by Katarzyna Sikora.

Transform data to long table format with reshape2 and generate the density plot with ggplot2:

limdat.CC.MeansL <- melt(limdat.CC.Means, variable.name = "Group", value.name = "Beta.Mean")
## No id variables; using all as measure variables
limdat.CC.MeansL$Group <- as.character(limdat.CC.MeansL$Group)
limdat.CC.MeansL$Group[limdat.CC.MeansL$Group %in% "MT"] <- "dnmt1m/m"
limdat.CC.MeansL$Group[limdat.CC.MeansL$Group %in% "WT"] <- "dnmt1+/+"
limdat.CC.MeansL$Group <- factor(limdat.CC.MeansL$Group, levels = c("dnmt1+/+", 
    "dnmt1m/m"))
ggplot(data = limdat.CC.MeansL, aes(x = Beta.Mean)) + geom_density(aes(group = Group, 
    colour = Group, fill = Group), alpha = 0.3) + ggtitle("All CG sites") + 
    theme(text = element_text(size = 14), axis.text = element_text(size = 11), 
        axis.title = element_text(size = 12)) + xlab("Mean methylation ratio") + 
    scale_colour_manual(values = c("blue", "red")) + scale_fill_manual(values = c("blue", 
    "red"))
